> <OLD>

> Hydras raissed his gun, he was ready for everything

<NEW>

And everything is what was comming at HYDRAS. In the front ranks are
wahat seemed to be literally hundreds of armored horns! Triceratops
and stegasaurai where leading the pack, followed by larger
tyranosaurases and other assorted and large reptiles. Hovering over
the group were flying reptiles, some as small as birds and some with
wings spans as large as 30 feet.

However station in the middle of all of that was singular creature, a
dinobot, around whom all the other creatures seemed to be moving. He
was floating about 30 feet above the center of the giant mass, his
optics dark and his arms folded over his chest.

The herd was still moving towards HYDRAS' base.

"Sire?" Inferno said as he stood next to HYDRAS, his ever faithful
guardian, "What are your orders?"

This was a sentiment that seemed echoed by many of the others. The
fuzors milled about, glancing between HYDRAS and SKYSHADOW, the fuzor
commander, a sense of dread apparent on their faces, the numbers here
were truely staggering.

CYCLONUS stood on the other side of HYDRAS, with DEEPSTRYKE, PHOBIA
and NIGHTRAZOR standing with him.

The rest of HYDRAS' men were kind spread about, glancing back at their
leader and then at the coming GIANT WAVE of dinosaur flesh.

(TAG)

Preston
